{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So, my question:"},{"time":2000,"text":"are we alone?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":4000,"text":"The story of humans is the story of ideas --"},{"time":8000,"text":"scientific ideas that shine light into dark corners,"},{"time":13000,"text":"ideas that we embrace rationally and irrationally,"},{"time":18000,"text":"ideas for which we've lived and died and killed and been killed,"},{"time":23000,"text":"ideas that have vanished in history,"},{"time":25000,"text":"and ideas that have been set in dogma."},{"time":29000,"text":"It's a story of nations,"},{"time":33000,"text":"of ideologies,"},{"time":37000,"text":"of territories,"},{"time":40000,"text":"and of conflicts among them."},{"time":45000,"text":"But, every moment of human history,"},{"time":49000,"text":"from the Stone Age to the Information Age,"},{"time":53000,"text":"from Sumer and Babylon to the iPod and celebrity gossip,"},{"time":58000,"text":"they've all been carried out --"},{"time":63000,"text":"every book that you've read,"},{"time":65000,"text":"every poem, every laugh, every tear --"},{"time":70000,"text":"they've all happened here."},{"time":74000,"text":"Here."},{"time":77000,"text":"Here."},{"time":81000,"text":"Here."},{"time":84000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"Perspective is a very powerful thing."},{"time":90000,"text":"Perspectives can change."},{"time":93000,"text":"Perspectives can be altered."},{"time":96000,"text":"From my perspective, we live on a fragile island of life,"},{"time":102000,"text":"in a universe of possibilities."},{"time":106000,"text":"For many millennia, humans have been on a journey to find answers,"},{"time":113000,"text":"answers to questions about naturalism and transcendence,"},{"time":118000,"text":"about who we are and why we are,"},{"time":122000,"text":"and of course, who else might be out there."},{"time":128000,"text":"Is it really just us?"},{"time":132000,"text":"Are we alone in this vast universe"},{"time":135000,"text":"of energy and matter and chemistry and physics?"},{"time":139000,"text":"Well, if we are, it's an awful waste of space."},{"time":143000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":145000,"text":"But, what if we're not?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"What if, out there, others are asking and answering similar questions?"},{"time":153000,"text":"What if they look up at the night sky, at the same stars,"},{"time":157000,"text":"but from the opposite side?"},{"time":160000,"text":"Would the discovery of an older cultural civilization out there"},{"time":168000,"text":"inspire us to find ways to survive"},{"time":173000,"text":"our increasingly uncertain technological adolescence?"},{"time":178000,"text":"Might it be the discovery of a distant civilization"},{"time":182000,"text":"and our common cosmic origins"},{"time":185000,"text":"that finally drives home the message of the bond among all humans?"},{"time":191000,"text":"Whether we're born in San Francisco, or Sudan,"},{"time":194000,"text":"or close to the heart of the Milky Way galaxy,"},{"time":197000,"text":"we are the products of a billion-year lineage of wandering stardust."},{"time":204000,"text":"We, all of us,"},{"time":207000,"text":"are what happens when a primordial mixture of hydrogen and helium"},{"time":211000,"text":"evolves for so long that it begins to ask where it came from."},{"time":217000,"text":"Fifty years ago,"},{"time":219000,"text":"the journey to find answers took a different path"},{"time":224000,"text":"and SETI, the Search for Extra-Terrestrial Intelligence,"},{"time":227000,"text":"began."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"So, what exactly is SETI?"},{"time":231000,"text":"Well, SETI uses the tools of astronomy"},{"time":234000,"text":"to try and find evidence of someone else's technology out there."},{"time":239000,"text":"Our own technologies are visible over interstellar distances,"},{"time":242000,"text":"and theirs might be as well."},{"time":245000,"text":"It might be that some massive network of communications,"},{"time":249000,"text":"or some shield against asteroidal impact,"},{"time":252000,"text":"or some huge astro-engineering project that we can't even begin to conceive of,"},{"time":257000,"text":"could generate signals at radio or optical frequencies"},{"time":261000,"text":"that a determined program of searching might detect."},{"time":265000,"text":"For millennia, we've actually turned to the priests and the philosophers"},{"time":269000,"text":"for guidance and instruction on this question of whether there's intelligent life out there."},{"time":275000,"text":"Now, we can use the tools of the 21st century to try and observe what is,"},{"time":281000,"text":"rather than ask what should be, believed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285000,"text":"SETI doesn't presume the existence of extra terrestrial intelligence;"},{"time":290000,"text":"it merely notes the possibility, if not the probability"},{"time":294000,"text":"in this vast universe, which seems fairly uniform."},{"time":298000,"text":"The numbers suggest a universe of possibilities."},{"time":301000,"text":"Our sun is one of 400 billion stars in our galaxy,"},{"time":307000,"text":"and we know that many other stars have planetary systems."},{"time":312000,"text":"We've discovered over 350 in the last 14 years,"},{"time":316000,"text":"including the small planet, announced earlier this week,"},{"time":322000,"text":"which has a radius just twice the size of the Earth."},{"time":326000,"text":"And, if even all of the planetary systems in our galaxy were devoid of life,"},{"time":335000,"text":"there are still 100 billion other galaxies out there,"},{"time":337000,"text":"altogether 10^22 stars."},{"time":340000,"text":"Now, I'm going to try a trick, and recreate an experiment from this morning."},{"time":345000,"text":"Remember, one billion?"},{"time":347000,"text":"But, this time not one billion dollars, one billion stars."},{"time":351000,"text":"Alright, one billion stars."},{"time":353000,"text":"Now, up there, 20 feet above the stage,"},{"time":356000,"text":"that's 10 trillion."},{"time":358000,"text":"Well, what about 10^22?"},{"time":361000,"text":"Where's the line that marks that?"},{"time":364000,"text":"That line would have to be 3.8 million miles above this stage."},{"time":370000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":371000,"text":"16 times farther away than the moon,"},{"time":374000,"text":"or four percent of the distance to the sun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376000,"text":"So, there are many possibilities."},{"time":379000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":381000,"text":"And much of this vast universe,"},{"time":384000,"text":"much more may be habitable than we once thought,"},{"time":387000,"text":"as we study extremophiles on Earth --"},{"time":389000,"text":"organisms that can live in conditions totally inhospitable for us,"},{"time":393000,"text":"in the hot, high pressure thermal vents at the bottom of the ocean,"},{"time":400000,"text":"frozen in ice, in boiling battery acid,"},{"time":404000,"text":"in the cooling waters of nuclear reactors."},{"time":408000,"text":"These extremophiles tell us that life may exist in many other environments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415000,"text":"But those environments are going to be widely spaced in this universe."},{"time":419000,"text":"Even our nearest star, the Sun --"},{"time":421000,"text":"its emissions suffer the tyranny of light speed."},{"time":426000,"text":"It takes a full eight minutes for its radiation to reach us."},{"time":429000,"text":"And the nearest star is 4.2 light years away,"},{"time":432000,"text":"which means its light takes 4.2 years to get here."},{"time":436000,"text":"And the edge of our galaxy is 75,000 light years away,"},{"time":440000,"text":"and the nearest galaxy to us, 2.5 million light years."},{"time":445000,"text":"That means any signal we detect would have started its journey a long time ago."},{"time":451000,"text":"And a signal would give us a glimpse of their past,"},{"time":456000,"text":"not their present."},{"time":458000,"text":"Which is why Phil Morrison calls SETI, \"the archaeology of the future.\""},{"time":463000,"text":"It tells us about their past,"},{"time":466000,"text":"but detection of a signal tells us it's possible for us to have a long future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474000,"text":"I think this is what David Deutsch meant in 2005,"},{"time":477000,"text":"when he ended his Oxford TEDTalk"},{"time":479000,"text":"by saying he had two principles he'd like to share for living,"},{"time":484000,"text":"and he would like to carve them on stone tablets."},{"time":487000,"text":"The first is that problems are inevitable."},{"time":491000,"text":"The second is that problems are soluble."},{"time":498000,"text":"So, ultimately what's going to determine the success or failure of SETI"},{"time":503000,"text":"is the longevity of technologies,"},{"time":507000,"text":"and the mean distance between technologies in the cosmos --"},{"time":513000,"text":"distance over space and distance over time."},{"time":517000,"text":"If technologies don't last and persist,"},{"time":520000,"text":"we will not succeed."},{"time":522000,"text":"And we're a very young technology"},{"time":524000,"text":"in an old galaxy,"},{"time":527000,"text":"and we don't yet know whether it's possible for technologies to persist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532000,"text":"So, up until now I've been talking to you about really large numbers."},{"time":537000,"text":"Let me talk about a relatively small number."},{"time":540000,"text":"And that's the length of time that the Earth was lifeless."},{"time":545000,"text":"Zircons that are mined in the Jack Hills of western Australia,"},{"time":552000,"text":"zircons taken from the Jack Hills of western Australia"},{"time":556000,"text":"tell us that within a few hundred million years of the origin of the planet"},{"time":561000,"text":"there was abundant water and perhaps even life."},{"time":564000,"text":"So, our planet has spent the vast majority of its 4.56 billion year history"},{"time":573000,"text":"developing life,"},{"time":575000,"text":"not anticipating its emergence."},{"time":577000,"text":"Life happened very quickly,"},{"time":579000,"text":"and that bodes well for the potential of life elsewhere in the cosmos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"And the other thing that one should take away from this chart"},{"time":589000,"text":"is the very narrow range of time"},{"time":593000,"text":"over which humans can claim to be the dominant intelligence on the planet."},{"time":597000,"text":"It's only the last few hundred thousand years"},{"time":601000,"text":"modern humans have been pursuing technology and civilization."},{"time":605000,"text":"So, one needs a very deep appreciation"},{"time":609000,"text":"of the diversity and incredible scale of life on this planet"},{"time":614000,"text":"as the first step in preparing to make contact with life elsewhere in the cosmos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623000,"text":"We are not the pinnacle of evolution."},{"time":629000,"text":"We are not the determined product"},{"time":633000,"text":"of billions of years of evolutionary plotting and planning."},{"time":638000,"text":"We are one outcome of a continuing adaptational process."},{"time":646000,"text":"We are residents of one small planet"},{"time":650000,"text":"in a corner of the Milky Way galaxy."},{"time":653000,"text":"And Homo sapiens are one small leaf"},{"time":658000,"text":"on a very extensive Tree of Life,"},{"time":662000,"text":"which is densely populated by organisms that have been honed for survival"},{"time":669000,"text":"over millions of years."},{"time":671000,"text":"We misuse language,"},{"time":674000,"text":"and talk about the \"ascent\" of man."},{"time":677000,"text":"We understand the scientific basis for the interrelatedness of life"},{"time":683000,"text":"but our ego hasn't caught up yet."},{"time":687000,"text":"So this \"ascent\" of man, pinnacle of evolution,"},{"time":691000,"text":"has got to go."},{"time":693000,"text":"It's a sense of privilege that the natural universe doesn't share."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698000,"text":"Loren Eiseley has said,"},{"time":701000,"text":"\"One does not meet oneself"},{"time":704000,"text":"until one catches the reflection from an eye other than human.\""},{"time":708000,"text":"One day that eye may be that of an intelligent alien,"},{"time":713000,"text":"and the sooner we eschew our narrow view of evolution"},{"time":719000,"text":"the sooner we can truly explore our ultimate origins and destinations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728000,"text":"We are a small part of the story of cosmic evolution,"},{"time":734000,"text":"and we are going to be responsible for our continued participation in that story,"},{"time":743000,"text":"and perhaps SETI will help as well."},{"time":746000,"text":"Occasionally, throughout history, this concept"},{"time":750000,"text":"of this very large cosmic perspective comes to the surface,"},{"time":754000,"text":"and as a result we see transformative and profound discoveries."},{"time":760000,"text":"So in 1543, Nicholas Copernicus published \"The Revolutions of Heavenly Spheres,\""},{"time":767000,"text":"and by taking the Earth out of the center,"},{"time":773000,"text":"and putting the sun in the center of the solar system,"},{"time":776000,"text":"he opened our eyes to a much larger universe,"},{"time":780000,"text":"of which we are just a small part."},{"time":783000,"text":"And that Copernican revolution continues today"},{"time":786000,"text":"to influence science and philosophy and technology and theology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791000,"text":"So, in 1959, Giuseppe Coccone and Philip Morrison"},{"time":796000,"text":"published the first SETI article in a refereed journal,"},{"time":800000,"text":"and brought SETI into the scientific mainstream."},{"time":803000,"text":"And in 1960, Frank Drake conducted the first SETI observation"},{"time":809000,"text":"looking at two stars, Tau Ceti and Epsilon Eridani,"},{"time":812000,"text":"for about 150 hours."},{"time":814000,"text":"Now Drake did not discover extraterrestrial intelligence,"},{"time":817000,"text":"but he learned a very valuable lesson from a passing aircraft,"},{"time":822000,"text":"and that's that terrestrial technology can interfere"},{"time":825000,"text":"with the search for extraterrestrial technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828000,"text":"We've been searching ever since,"},{"time":830000,"text":"but it's impossible to overstate the magnitude of the search that remains."},{"time":835000,"text":"All of the concerted SETI efforts, over the last 40-some years,"},{"time":839000,"text":"are equivalent to scooping a single glass of water from the oceans."},{"time":844000,"text":"And no one would decide that the ocean was without fish"},{"time":848000,"text":"on the basis of one glass of water."},{"time":850000,"text":"The 21st century now allows us to build bigger glasses --"},{"time":855000,"text":"much bigger glasses."},{"time":857000,"text":"In Northern California, we're beginning to take observations"},{"time":862000,"text":"with the first 42 telescopes of the Allen Telescope Array --"},{"time":866000,"text":"and I've got to take a moment right now to publicly thank"},{"time":870000,"text":"Paul Allen and Nathan Myhrvold"},{"time":872000,"text":"and all the TeamSETI members in the TED community"},{"time":875000,"text":"who have so generously supported this research."},{"time":879000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":888000,"text":"The ATA is the first telescope built from a large number of small dishes,"},{"time":892000,"text":"and hooked together with computers."},{"time":894000,"text":"It's making silicon as important as aluminum,"},{"time":896000,"text":"and we'll grow it in the future by adding more antennas to reach 350"},{"time":902000,"text":"for more sensitivity and leveraging Moore's law for more processing capability."},{"time":907000,"text":"Today, our signal detection algorithms"},{"time":911000,"text":"can find very simple artifacts and noise."},{"time":914000,"text":"If you look very hard here you can see the signal from the Voyager 1 spacecraft,"},{"time":919000,"text":"the most distant human object in the universe,"},{"time":923000,"text":"106 times as far away from us as the sun is."},{"time":928000,"text":"And over those long distances, its signal is very faint when it reaches us."},{"time":933000,"text":"It may be hard for your eye to see it,"},{"time":935000,"text":"but it's easily found with our efficient algorithms."},{"time":938000,"text":"But this is a simple signal,"},{"time":940000,"text":"and tomorrow we want to be able to find more complex signals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":944000,"text":"This is a very good year."},{"time":947000,"text":"2009 is the 400th anniversary of Galileo's first use of the telescope,"},{"time":954000,"text":"Darwin's 200th birthday,"},{"time":957000,"text":"the 150th anniversary of the publication of \"On the Origin of Species,\""},{"time":962000,"text":"the 50th anniversary of SETI as a science,"},{"time":965000,"text":"the 25th anniversary of the incorporation of the SETI Institute as a non-profit,"},{"time":971000,"text":"and of course, the 25th anniversary of TED."},{"time":974000,"text":"And next month, the Kepler Spacecraft will launch"},{"time":977000,"text":"and will begin to tell us just how frequent Earth-like planets are,"},{"time":982000,"text":"the targets for SETI's searches."},{"time":984000,"text":"In 2009, the U.N. has declared it to be the International Year of Astronomy,"},{"time":991000,"text":"a global festival to help us residents of Earth"},{"time":995000,"text":"rediscover our cosmic origins and our place in the universe."},{"time":999000,"text":"And in 2009, change has come to Washington,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"with a promise to put science in its rightful position."},{"time":1008000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009000,"text":"So, what would change everything?"},{"time":1011000,"text":"Well, this is the question the Edge foundation asked this year,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"and four of the respondents said, \"SETI.\""},{"time":1018000,"text":"Why?"},{"time":1020000,"text":"Well, to quote:"},{"time":1022000,"text":"\"The discovery of intelligent life beyond Earth"},{"time":1024000,"text":"would eradicate the loneliness and solipsism"},{"time":1026000,"text":"that has plagued our species since its inception."},{"time":1029000,"text":"And it wouldn't simply change everything,"},{"time":1031000,"text":"it would change everything all at once.\""},{"time":1034000,"text":"So, if that's right, why did we only capture four out of those 151 minds?"},{"time":1041000,"text":"I think it's a problem of completion and delivery,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"because the fine print said,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"\"What game-changing ideas and scientific developments"},{"time":1052000,"text":"would you expect to live to see?\""},{"time":1054000,"text":"So, we have a fulfillment problem."},{"time":1057000,"text":"We need bigger glasses and more hands in the water,"},{"time":1060000,"text":"and then working together, maybe we can all live to see"},{"time":1063000,"text":"the detection of the first extraterrestrial signal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1067000,"text":"That brings me to my wish."},{"time":1071000,"text":"I wish that you would empower Earthlings everywhere"},{"time":1076000,"text":"to become active participants"},{"time":1080000,"text":"in the ultimate search for cosmic company."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1083000,"text":"The first step would be to tap into the global brain trust,"},{"time":1088000,"text":"to build an environment where raw data could be stored,"},{"time":1092000,"text":"and where it could be accessed and manipulated,"},{"time":1095000,"text":"where new algorithms could be developed and old algorithms made more efficient."},{"time":1100000,"text":"And this is a technically creative challenge,"},{"time":1103000,"text":"and it would change the perspective of people who worked on it."},{"time":1106000,"text":"And then, we'd like to augment the automated search with human insight."},{"time":1115000,"text":"We'd like to use the pattern recognition capability of the human eye"},{"time":1121000,"text":"to find faint, complex signals that our current algorithms miss."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1127000,"text":"And, of course, we'd like to inspire and engage the next generation."},{"time":1132000,"text":"We'd like to take the materials that we have built for education,"},{"time":1139000,"text":"and get them out to students everywhere,"},{"time":1142000,"text":"students that can't come and visit us at the ATA."},{"time":1145000,"text":"We'd like to tell our story better,"},{"time":1147000,"text":"and engage young people, and thereby change their perspective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1151000,"text":"I'm sorry Seth Godin, but over the millennia, we've seen where tribalism leads."},{"time":1156000,"text":"We've seen what happens when we divide an already small planet"},{"time":1160000,"text":"into smaller islands."},{"time":1162000,"text":"And, ultimately, we actually all belong to only one tribe,"},{"time":1168000,"text":"to Earthlings."},{"time":1170000,"text":"And SETI is a mirror --"},{"time":1172000,"text":"a mirror that can show us ourselves"},{"time":1175000,"text":"from an extraordinary perspective,"},{"time":1177000,"text":"and can help to trivialize the differences among us."},{"time":1182000,"text":"If SETI does nothing but change the perspective of humans on this planet,"},{"time":1189000,"text":"then it will be one of the most profound endeavors in history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1194000,"text":"So, in the opening days of 2009,"},{"time":1198000,"text":"a visionary president stood on the steps of the U.S. Capitol"},{"time":1202000,"text":"and said, \"We cannot help but believe"},{"time":1205000,"text":"that the old hatreds shall someday pass,"},{"time":1208000,"text":"that the lines of tribe shall soon dissolve,"},{"time":1212000,"text":"that, as the world grows smaller, our common humanity shall reveal itself.\""},{"time":1218000,"text":"So, I look forward to working with the TED community"},{"time":1220000,"text":"to hear about your ideas about how to fulfill this wish,"},{"time":1224000,"text":"and in collaborating with you,"},{"time":1228000,"text":"hasten the day that that visionary statement can become a reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1233000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1235000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}